name: Not a basis for invalidation of identification or suppression of identification evidence Confidentiality
text: [§844D-74]  Not a basis for invalidation of identification or suppression of identification evidence.  Nothing in this part shall be construed to invalidate an otherwise valid identification of a person by means of DNA testing or to provide the basis for a suppression of otherwise admissible evidence related to identification of a person based on DNA testing. [L 2005, c 112, pt of §1]
